[{"id":"IKF000000","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"long_descriptions_container\"></div></div><div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <div class=\"standalone_image qti-align-center\"><img alt=\"Graph of a circle and a right triangle in the x y plane with the origin labeled O. Both the axes range from 0 to 1 in increments of 1. The circle has its center at the origin and is of radius 1. Refer to long description.\" aria-describedby=\"LDC-IKF000000_01\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/IKF000000_01.svg\"/><div class=\"sr-only qti-visually-hidden\" id=\"LDC-IKF000000_01\" role=\"region\"><ul>\n<li>The circle passes through the points (1 comma 0) and (0 comma 1).</li>\n<li>Point Q is on the x axis between the origin and (1 comma 0).</li>\n<li>Point P is at the intersection of the circle and a ray from the origin into the first quadrant.</li>\n<li>A segment from point P to point Q is perpendicular to the x axis.</li>\n<li>A right triangle is formed by the origin, point P, and point Q.</li>\n</ul></div></div><p class=\"dap_body\">​</p><p class=\"dap_body\">​</p><p class=\"dap_body\">​The figure shows the terminal ray of an angle in standard position intersecting the unit circle at point <span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\"><semantics><mi>P</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> in the <span aria-label=\"x y\"><math alttext=\"x y\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>-plane. Segment <span aria-label=\"P Q\"><math alttext=\"P Q\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> is perpendicular to the <span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\"><semantics><mi>x</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>-axis. A triangle is formed by the points at the origin, <span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\"><semantics><mi>P</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>, and <span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\"><semantics><mi>Q</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>. The function <span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><semantics><mi>A</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> gives the area of the triangle, <span aria-label=\"A open parentheses theta close parentheses\"><math alttext=\"A open parentheses theta close parentheses\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>, based on the measure of the angle <span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\"><semantics><mi>θ</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>, in radians. What is the value of <span aria-label=\"A open parentheses pi over 3 close parentheses\"><math alttext=\"A open parentheses pi over 3 close parentheses\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> ? (Note: The area of a triangle with base <span aria-label=\"b\"><math alttext=\"b\"><semantics><mi>b</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> and height <span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\"><semantics><mi>h</mi><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span> is <span aria-label=\"A equals 1 half b h\"><math alttext=\"A equals 1 half b h\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span>.)</p> </div> </div> </div>\n","rubricRef":"IKF000000_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"dap_body\">​<span aria-label=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 8 end fraction\"><math alttext=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 8 end fraction\"><semantics><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>8</mn></mfrac><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span></p>","<p class=\"dap_body\">​<span aria-label=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 4 end fraction\"><math alttext=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 4 end fraction\"><semantics><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span></p>","<p class=\"dap_body\">​<span aria-label=\"1 half\"><math alttext=\"1 half\"><semantics><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span></p>","<p class=\"dap_body\">​<span aria-label=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 2 end fraction\"><math alttext=\"fraction numerator square root of 3 over denominator 2 end fraction\"><semantics><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><annotation encoding=\"application/vnd.wiris.mtweb-params+json\">{\"digitSeparatorsAsMN\":\"auto\"}</annotation></semantics></math></span></p>"],"answer":"A-89438"}]